<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The mhd_assert macro is defined as ((void)0) in the provided headers. Therefore the statement
    mhd_assert ((pool->size - _MHD_RED_ZONE_SIZE) >= (old_offset + old_size));
expands to a no-op; it is executed (reachable) but has no effect and its removal would not change program behaviour. This is dead code and thus violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2. (If mhd_assert were defined to perform a runtime check in some builds, then this particular instance would not be dead; with the given definition it is.)
</scenario>
